Re: Bitcoin Address Collisions

Bitcointalk

2010-02-23 22:24:00 UTC - [11]Original Post

   [12]Quote from: NewLibertyStandard on February 23, 2010, 07:04:47 PM
   Are generated bitcoins encrypted with whichever address is currently
   displayed in the main Bitcoin window?
   No, each generated transaction uses a new, single-use address.
   Nothing uses the address in the main window, itʼs just there for
   convenience for you to copy.  0.2.5 has a "New..." button next to it to
   make it easy to change each time you use it.
